Windows MiniBrowser: enable WebGPU runtime feature by default.

The Apple Win port ships with WebGPU's runtime feature flag disabled,
so navigator.gpu.requestAdapter() returns null on every launch even
though the binding is exposed. The InternalFeatures dialog can flip
the bit at runtime but the change is in-memory only -- WebKitBrowserWindow
does not persist it.

Set WebGPUEnabled=true on the freshly-created WKPreferencesRef in
WebKitBrowserWindow::create() before it is bound to the page
configuration. This is the only path that runs before the first
navigation and is independent of the menu/UI state.

The preference key is "WebGPUEnabled", taken verbatim from
Source/WTF/Scripts/Preferences/UnifiedWebPreferences.yaml.

diff --git a/Tools/MiniBrowser/win/WebKitBrowserWindow.cpp b/Tools/MiniBrowser/win/WebKitBrowserWindow.cpp
--- a/Tools/MiniBrowser/win/WebKitBrowserWindow.cpp
+++ b/Tools/MiniBrowser/win/WebKitBrowserWindow.cpp
@@ -148,6 +148,13 @@
     auto preferences = adoptWK(WKPreferencesCreate());
     WKPreferencesSetMediaCapabilitiesEnabled(preferences.get(), false);
     WKPreferencesSetDeveloperExtrasEnabled(preferences.get(), true);
+    // webkitium: turn on the WebGPU runtime feature so navigator.gpu
+    // requestAdapter() resolves on first launch.  The InternalFeatures
+    // dialog only mutates this in-memory and does not persist.
+    {
+        auto webGPUKey = adoptWK(WKStringCreateWithUTF8CString("WebGPUEnabled"));
+        WKPreferencesSetExperimentalFeatureForKey(preferences.get(), true, webGPUKey.get());
+    }
 
     auto pageConf = adoptWK(WKPageConfigurationCreate());
     WKPageConfigurationSetWebsiteDataStore(pageConf.get(), websiteDataStore.get());
